Do the characters know, that the temple is devoted to an archdevil? An
archdevil is evil incarnate. People who worship a devil can't be good.
People who even support a devil can't be good. Ending the cult is a
good thing! The big question is: How do they do it?

My question is: How do the characters act? If they have no knowledge
of the devil and start killing cultists without a simple conversation
(like: "We know you worship evil! Repent! Step aside, we'll burn down
this sacrilege."), they are probably neutral or even evil. They should
at the very least have the intention to do good by killing the cultist
and they should show the intention via roleplaying. If they start to
enjoy killing without making sure that they kill the "right guy", well
that's evil.

An example: Winter. Near a small human village the group encounters a
bunch of 13 goblins. First round in combat drops the leader of the
goblins, they start to flee. Would it be good to let them escape? The
human paladin of the group hunts down the majority of the goblins
until they don't pose a threat to the village. Did he commit an act of
evil? or good? He wanted to protect the village, so he did the right
thing. If he hadn't mentioned his intention, well than it would
probably be an act of evil.
--
